<concept id="concept_D7BC95FA5F044A9F86C6D7B26EE2B095"> 
  <title>Localization Checklist</title> 
  <shortdesc>Steps that must be performed when sending webhelp to
	 localizations. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <conbody> 
	 <p>Contact Melissa Baerwald for localization schedules, budgets, etc. 
	 </p> 
	 <table id="table_B679062C33C6476EB470A525650E397A"> 
		<tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col01" colnum="1"
		  colwidth="1.00*"/><colspec colnum="2" colname="col1" colwidth="2.68*"/><colspec
		  colnum="3" colname="col2" colwidth="5.78*"/><thead> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">Step 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Task 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2">Notes 
				</entry> 
			 </row></thead> 
		  <tbody> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">1
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">
				  <p>In XMetaL, run Acrocheck over all topics. 
				  </p>
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2">
				  <p>Rick Brough is the process lead for Acrocheck.
				  </p>
				  <p>See 
					 <xref
					  href="c_acrolinx.xml#concept_C7F44210A48449A7919D430B28D5C534" format="dita"
					  scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Acrolinx plug-in for XMetaL?></xref>.
				  </p>
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">2
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">
				  <p>Run link checker and check all links. 
				  </p>
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2">
				  <p>Link errors are the main reason the vendor requires
					 re-posting. 
				  </p>
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">3
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Build help and run index. 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2">The webhelp you send must be an indexed,
				  publishable version. 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">4
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Get a clean copy of indexed output. 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2"> Copy all files in webhelp from 
				  <xref
					href="file://obudoc.corp.adobe.com/t2/help/en_US">\\obudoc.corp.adobe.com\t2\help\en_US</xref>
				  
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">5 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Locate source graphics (Illustrator) and copy
				  them to the 
				  <term>graphics</term> folder in the ouptut. 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2"> 
				  <p>Your source can be Illustrator, Snag-it, or whatever eases the
					 vendor's pain. Where possible, first send homemade graphics to UX, and ask for
					 an Illustrator copy in return. 
				  </p> 
				  <p><b>Caution</b>: If you have multiple ditamaps in one project
					 (if you combined two projects), verify that all links to graphics point to a 
					 <filepath>.png</filepath> in a common 
					 <term>graphics</term> folder. Case sensitivity matters on the
					 folder name when you publish live. (Use lower case by default on all file and
					 directory names.) 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">6
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Zip the webhelp out folder. 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2">Include all files and folders created in the
				  webhelp out build. 
				  <p>Name the folder so that it's easy to identify. For example: 
				  </p> 
				  <p> 
					 <codeblock>20130825_analytics_reference.zip</codeblock> 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">7
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Create a folder location on 
				  <filepath>/gftp/_products/DMS</filepath> 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2">Use Filezilla to access gftp site. 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">8
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Copy the zipped output. 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2"> Example: 
				  <p> 
					 <codeblock>/gftp/_products/DMS/20130524_social</codeblock> 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">9
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Create a file system directory in
				  WorldServer. 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2"> 
				  <p>Example: 
				  </p> 
				  <p> 
					 <codeblock>/Help/inbox/OBU/social/20130524</codeblock> 
				  </p> 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">10
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Upload the zipped output. 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2"> 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row> 
				<entry colname="col01">11
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col1">Notify vendor 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="col2">Use standard template emails. 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
		  </tbody> 
		</tgroup> 
	 </table> 
  </conbody>
</concept>
